content: Sequels never work. Period. But this one did. From the visuals, the music, quirkiness of it, it's brilliant. For me, the icing on the top is the eventual return to the first game, with different puzzles to solve. But! An Easter Egg! In one of the bedrooms you can switch the music back to the original if you click on the radio. By far the best game Fire Maple have done.
Great game , the hints help but was fun and challenging

I've played dozens of games like this and there is something so oddly special about this one. Extremely creative and clever use of items, definitely requires some outside of the box thinking. Usually games as linear as this one can be either too simple or too frustrating if you get stuck on a complicated puzzle, but even when I was unsure what to do, I was thoroughly enjoying the challenge. Oh and I was SO pleased with the length! Keep up the outstanding work, Fire Maple!
This game was very fun to play. The graphics, gameplay, and storyline were absolutely marvelous!

Really enjoyable game and nice bonus at the end. The only negative thing I would say is that when you've purchased the game it would be better if you didn't have to wait so long between hints. I mean, why? It's not as if they're getting revenue from adverts during the time (thank goodness)

Big fan of Fire Maple Games. This is another great addition to the series of adventure puzzle games. Hint button works well (even with the time delay!) and even without the use of a magic map, it was still fun to play.

A VAST improvement on the first Grisly Manor, this one is long and creative, fun story line and puzzles, nice graphics. What a fun, humorous game! Some puzzle solutions made me chuckle they were so cute. Loved it! Great job Maple games. I really enjoyed the Lost City too.

I used to play them when I was little, and going back to the old house and being able to adjust it to the old music was EVERYTHING. Thank you so much for this game, and I hope to see more soon!! :))

A great followup to the original Grisly Manor.  You get to explore the new renovated house and go back to the old house.  The puzzles are straightforward and intuitive, though not extremely challenging.  A great game that isn't frustrating, but does get your mind working.
Fire maples best so far

A return to a good game, the puzzles were a little hard(quite a few were easy,) i wasn't expecting the end, but was hopeing for it. Some of the objectives seemed somewhat stupid, but all in all, it was a good game i'd say. I really think you could have kept a few things the same as in the old game, but thats my own opinion, but all in all, it was a good game.

Fire Maple has a winner!  Lots of intuitive puzzles, brightly lit with plenty of gameplay- this is one of Fire Maple's best.  It's a real pleasure to play a genuine puzzle / adventure game without any hidden object scenes, with at least a bit of a storyline.  Free recharging hints for when you need them.

Another great FireMaple game.  Was very excited to go back to the mansion.  Throwbacks to other games were really cool.  A few of the clues were really tough and didn't make sense to me but overall game was fun!  Looking forward to Gramps's next adventure!

I don't like how the game artificially stonewalls you from completing a puzzle even if you know the solution, and I'm really eager to do another few runs through this game with sequence breaking but the game won't let me.

If you are a fan of the first, you'll really enjoy the sequel. The puzzles are challenging and the story is fun. The only downside is that there is no cloud save and no cloud sync. So, progress on one device does not carry over to another device. And uninstalls or system restores result in loosing all progress. I can't seem to find a way to skip ahead to where I left off.

It was still a very enjoyable game. I love Fire Maple Games!

I played the first Grisly Manor on the Amazon app store and was grabbed by it. The perfect exploration problem solving puzzler with a good story.  This one is at least as good and maybe even better.  Hoping for more!

My favourite game of the year. Built with love and an amazing attention to detail, this game is huge compared to the original. In fact, there was one point when I thought it had finished and it turned out it was just the end of the first part!  Very easy to use, the story has lots of humour and the puzzles are ingenious. An absolute masterpiece.

Mostly Great game & a real challenge at times - far surpasses the first. Worth the money with no annoying ads. Even had to use a couple of hints. Much harder than the last one which is great and it almost never ends. The fun just continues!

Can't get enough from this developer, so much fun trying to figure out the twists and turns and item combinations to solve each piece of the puzzle.  The throw backs to the previous games are such a cool element.  Even my middle school aged kiddos love these games!
